productsList.title: What's IP

Waste and Chemicals Inspection Tool (Watch-IT)

ABOUT

This app is developed to support law enforcement officers when performing inspections of shipments of waste and chemicals that are covered by the Basel, Rotterdam and Stockholm Conventions and related regional agreements. It merely offers guidance and references and does not aim to offer legal or binding advice in any way, form, or shape. 

TO THE POINT

Legislation can be complex and lengthy. This app zooms in on the legal provisions relevant for shipments of waste and chemicals during a first assessment by inspectors and law enforcement officers. 

For example:

â€¢	What are the requirements for imports and exports of waste and chemicals?
â€¢	What are legal definitions of (hazardous) waste and chemicals?
â€¢	What is illegal traffic?

REFERENCES

This app provides searchable databases with all annexes containing waste and chemicals, covered by the scope of international and regional agreements. You can search by waste code, chemicals code, customs code or name. It also includes a variety of references, such as guidelines and example documents. 

CHECKLISTS

It provides points of attention what to look out for when performing administrative and physical checks of shipments of waste or chemicals.

Some key features:

â€¢	Waste stream library â€“ providing information and photos of 20 priority and /or problematic waste streams
â€¢	Database with hazardous characteric classes and symbols
â€¢	Contact database - containing contact details of environmental authorities and/or customs authorities, including links to their websites. 

FEEDBACK ON THE APP

In case you notice any outdated information, gaps or errors in the information provided, or anything else you would want to share with us, please contacts us by: info@ambiendura.com

Any feedback on the use of the app is also welcomed!

Note for .PAK file extension: This app DOES NOT open video game PAK files. PAK files could be video game packages or packed files. This app only opens packed files and not video game packages.

After the free full trial expires, the app becomes the limited trial, in which the creating new zip files function is locked. Anytime in both free full trial and limited trial, you can purchase a full license (US $1.49 - $7.99) to upgrade the app to the full version.

Features:
 - Easy-to-use file manager
 - Familiar GUI like Windows Explorer
 - Browse, open, view and extract all kinds of archive files
 - Rar, Zip, 7z, Iso, Bzip2, Gzip, Pak, Tar, Xz and more supported

 - Partial extraction

Note: the file compression feature of this app can only create new Zip format files but no other formats.

productsList.title: JOSM
productsList.description:
JOSM is an extensible editor for OpenStreetMap (OSM) in Java.

It supports loading GPX tracks, background imagery, and OSM data from local sources as well as from online sources and allows to edit the OSM data (nodes, ways, and relations) and their metadata tags.

JOSM is translated by the community in more than 40 languages.

It is open source and licensed under GPL: https://josm.openstreetmap.de/
